Exercise 4: Study a convergence of the absorption spectrum of Na2 molecule

Study the convergence of the absorption spectrum of Na2 with respect to:

a) The number of Lanczos iterations itermax = 50, 100, 150, ...
   without using the extrapolation (extrapolation='no');  
b) The number of Lanczos iterations when the extrapolation 
   is used (extrapolation='osc');
c) The size of the supercell: celldm(1) = 20, 30, 40, ...


Step 1. Runc the SCF ground-state calculation

   mpirun -np 2 /scratch/timrov/QE_tmp7_6.0/qe-6.0/bin/pw.x < Na2.scf.in > Na2.scf.out

Step 2. Perform Lanczos recursions

   mpirun -np 2 /scratch/timrov/QE_tmp7_6.0/qe-6.0/bin/turbo_lanczos.x < Na2.lanczos.in > Na2.lanczos.out

Step 3. Run the spectrum calculation

   /scratch/timrov/QE_tmp7_6.0/qe-6.0/bin/turbo_spectrum.x < Na2.tddfpt_pp.in > Na2.tddfpt_pp.out

Step 4. Plot the spectrum

    Note, in this example we compute the response of the system along three directions (X,Y,Z).
    Therefore, extract the oscillator strength S(E) from the file Na2.plot_chi.dat:

    grep 'S(E)' Na2.plot_chi.dat > Na2.plot_S.dat 

    gnuplot -> load 'plot_spectrum.gnu'

    evince Na2_spectrum.eps

